---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout 
  title="About - The Web Talk Show"
  description="The Web Talk Show is an interview podcast exploring behind-the-scenes insights across tech, AI, business operations, design, and leadership. Hosted by Armando J. Perez-Carreno."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="font-[var(--font-display)] font-extrabold text-4xl sm:text-5xl tracking-tight mb-8" style="color: var(--text-heading);">About The Web Talk Show</h1>
      
      <div class="prose max-w-none space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-heading);">What This Is</h2>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">
            The Web Talk Show is an interview podcast exploring behind-the-scenes insights from different industries. 
            Each episode features conversations with founders, engineers, designers, and business operators who share 
            practical knowledge about their work, their industries, and the systems they've built.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text);">
            Episodes are available in both video and audio formats, typically running 30-60 minutes, 
            with new episodes released weekly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-heading);">Who This Is For</h2>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text);">
            The show serves entrepreneurs, business owners, technology professionals, and curious minds 
            interested in learning how things work in practice â€” not just in theory. Listeners include 
            developers, designers, product managers, and anyone building or operating technology-driven businesses.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-heading);">Topics Covered</h2>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color: var(--text);">
            Conversations span a range of industries and specialties, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-lg" style="color: var(--text);">
            <li>Technology and software development</li>
            <li>Artificial intelligence and automation</li>
            <li>Business operations and systems</li>
            <li>Design and user experience</li>
            <li>WordPress and web platforms</li>
            <li>Marketing and growth</li>
            <li>Leadership and team building</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-heading);">History</h2>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text);">
            The Web Talk Show launched in May 2024 and has published over 56 episodes featuring guests from 
            companies, agencies, and projects across the technology and business landscape.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-heading);">Where to Listen</h2>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-6">
            <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/00BTCbkMIG7mjeTP9zlsIq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors" style="background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text);" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#1DB954'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='var(--border)'">
              <span class="font-medium">Spotify</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-web-talk-show/id1822997923" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors" style="background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text);" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#fc3c44'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='var(--border)'">
              <span class="font-medium">Apple Podcasts</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1CI93sNrODNNJppF8HFcDKDHQVHLHN8v" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors" style="background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text);" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#FF0000'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='var(--border)'">
              <span class="font-medium">YouTube</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--text-heading);">The Host</h2>
          <div class="not-prose flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center sm:items-start gap-6 p-6 rounded-xl" style="background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
            <img 
              src="/armando.jpg" 
              alt="Armando J. Perez-Carreno" 
              class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full object-cover ring-2 ring-[#e63329]/20 flex-shrink-0"
            />
            <div class="text-center sm:text-left">
              <h3 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-heading);">Armando J. Perez-Carreno</h3>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-base" style="color: var(--text);">
                Armando J. Perez-Carreno is a business automation consultant who helps companies eliminate 
                operational bottlenecks and scale more efficiently through custom AI automation systems. 
                He works with business owners to design and implement automation workflows tailored to their 
                specific operational needs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
